Process called "get_all_environment_variables_internal" returns Dictionary[String, String]:
    Note: Get all environment variables with essential runtime calls
    Try:
        Let env_vars be dictionary containing
        Let common_vars be list containing "PATH", "HOME", "USER", "PWD", "SHELL", "TERM"
        
        For each var_name in common_vars:
            Let var_value be system_call_environment_get with name as var_name
            If var_value is not None:
                Set env_vars[var_name] to var_value
        
        Return env_vars
    Catch error:
        Note: Return minimal environment on error
        Return dictionary containing:
            "PATH" as "/usr/bin:/bin"
            "HOME" as "/home/user"
            "USER" as "user"

Process called "get_home_directory_internal" returns String:
